Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update apt and install Python + pytest dependencies
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create initial directory layout and raw CSV files for the exercise
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    mkdir -p /home/user/datasets/raw

    # experiment_A.csv
    cat > /home/user/datasets/raw/experiment_A.csv <<'EOF'
ID,Value
A1,10
A2,15
A3,N/A
A4,20
EOF

    # experiment_B.csv
    cat > /home/user/datasets/raw/experiment_B.csv <<'EOF'
ID,Value
B1,5
B2,8
B3,11
B4,N/A
B5,12
EOF

    # Ensure the student can create additional files/directories
    chmod -R a+rwx /home/user

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author  "Apptainer Task Prep"
    Description "Container pre-configured with raw CSV files and pytest for the data-cleaning exercise."

%help
This container provides the starting environment for the data-cleaning task.
Raw datasets are located under /home/user/datasets/raw/.
Pytest is installed system-wide for automated grading.